76561198164948371,Not Recommended,413030,20684503,"Posted: 22 January, 2016",all,Ropo,"So, I bought this game when it ""re launched"" last year. The game is not bad, but it isn't very good either. Like the RPG/turn based idea. It gets annoying when you don't get the stones/cards you need and you are e.g. lvl 12 and get killed by sth lvl 10. Also, the regeneration bonus is ridiculous. 4hp in 1500 hp (lvl 15) every few seconds? Start another game, go out , watch a movie or read a book while you heal, because if you go b to base, all the creatures respawn.Apart from some serious lag issues, which got me killed several times, there are almost no people playing it. So how come you have an ""online only"" game with no people online? I already knew that few people were playing, but I never imagined such a little number. All the players of my lvl or of similar lvl I asked for a party declined it. Moreover, there are very few weapons and equipment available, not even one per lvl.Apart from this, they elevated the price from 3.99 or 4.99 to 9.99, so that they could release some DLC at 4.99 ONE month later... I cannot support any company that does that kind of shady things. Besides, the basic game just gets you to lvl 30, while the DLC pushes it to 40, so you'll have to buy at least 5 more DLC packs. For me it's either launch the whole game or just don't... Selling content that could have been added when the game was launched is just wrong for me.So, rounding up, I would only recomend this game if you buy it when it's on sale, and if you have some friends to play it with.Hope I helped."
