76561198045999415,Recommended,413030,19766088,"Posted: 18 December, 2015",all,Elephiant,"Mytheon is a Hack and Slash MMO RPG with strategy elements set in ancient greece with evil gods and courageous heroes. You play one of these heroes and your goal is to defeat the gods.TLDR:- Gameplay may feel stiff/boring at first, but when playing a little longer with more challanging situations the strategy in the game comes out better. The stones collections, towers, companions and abilities certainly make a nice mix to play with. Shame there are few people though.- graphics are okay though not impressive when global lightning is overwhelming. More moody areas look fairly nice.- Music doesn't really draw my attention so far, but it's not bad.= Though it's not a GREAT game it deserves more attention than that it has now. You may find this game♥♥♥♥♥♥and boring, but it can also be quite interesting, unique and fun to play.There are 3 classes to choose from (I've only played the Elementalist, so I might be a little unclear about the other classes):- Warcaster: heavy equipment, melee fighting- Eidolon: between Warcaster and Elementalist- Elemetalist: focuses on spells, towers and companions, quick mana regenThe basic gameplay is just to smash every monster you see and take all loot like in many other hack and slash rpg games. Leveling up simply increases your stats, nothing shiny there. What makes this game interesting (besides it's setting in greece if that interests you) is the stones you can collect. Sounds boring? Didn't catch me at first either :p. However there are stones you can collect and put in you ""batte set"". Your battle set is a set of stones you can use during battle. For it to be usable it has to contain between 15 and 40 stones. On the bottom of the screen 6 stones are displayed. These stones are randomly picked from your battle set. You can activate them (if you aren't in a safe area) by clicking them or by pressing there corresponding number 1-6.There are basically 3 types of stones:- Companion: summons a companion to fight beside you. By pressing F you select all companions and by clicking on anywhere else you deselect all companions and select yourself. You can move yourself and each of you companions seperately like you do with units in an RTS. Companions disappear after a certain time and have different HPs.- Towers: towers are the same as companions except that they can't move and often do more damage and have higher HP.- Abilities: abilities like in any other RPG game.You start with a basic battle set of 15 stones and can find more in loot. You can also craft stones by using ingredients or by creating them out of 2 or more other stones.Companions can be of 3 different types:- attacker- defender- rangedthese types follow Rock Paper Scissor:- attacker GOOD AGAINST ranged- defender GOOD AGAINST attacker- ranged GOOD AGAINST defenderI'm not yet shure about the damage types, but there are 6 listed of which 4 are elemental:- melee- ranged- fire- water- air- plantwater GOOD AGAINST firefire GOOD AGAINST airair GOOD AGAINST plantplant GOOD AGAINST waterAll companions, spells tower, and weapons can do elemental damage (not necesarily) and all can have/boost resistances.This makes it important to choose the righ way to attack, because (e.g.) fire against fire does very little damage.You can trade with NPC's (in the hub) and put items on sale for other players (or buy their items) by paying a small fee. Beside the standard coop gameplay you can play pvp 1v1 or 2v2 in an arena. Haven't tried this yet because currently there are simply to few players. There is a tutorial, though it's all in text, so for the less patient (like me) it might be less fun to learn the basics. Certain tutorial text pops up when you visit certain areas. It's all explained pretty straight forward in few words, so it's not that bad. All tutorial text can be found in the journal at any time as well.Though the music is made by Frank Klepacki it didn't really stick with me. It also seems that there are very few tracks, the music feels repetitive. It's not bad, but (so far) I didn't really draw my attention. Though it's a 2010 game the graphics didn't impress me at all at first. When you get a little further in the game and there are more lightning effects, it looks fairly nice though."
76561198059109737,Recommended,413030,25761438,"Posted: 28 September, 2016",all,konnermoshier,This game is great! i played it when it orignally launched and i was sad to see it shut down. One thing that would be great is if you could play it offline too! also a play with a friend via lan would be a nice offline  idea
