76561197999482187,Recommended,413030,20071871,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,Porro,"This review may be a bet lengthy, but only because all is not as it appears. I will include a TL;DR for all your ""helmet-wearing, crayon eating, Mommy's little snowflake types"".First and foremost, this is most definitely an MMO in the vein of an instanced dungeon-crawler. (Think Path of Exile/Diablo 2-3, etc.) The game is based upon mythology ranging from Ancient Greece to Egypt (Though that content has yet to be launched, the ability to access the NPC to go to the hub is in-game.) Instead of standard abilities and levels, this game uses ""stones""; think cards that are randomly dealt to your from your ""deck"" (Active Stone Set). The game is most definitely designed to be difficult but fair, and will not cater to the weak! (One of the strongest points in my opinion.) After level 10~, this game really starts to push the whole MMO concept, IE working in pairs/groups. Without one, you will struggle/trudge through the dungeons as the difficulty INSTANTLY goes up. This should not discourage those looking to play single-player, however let it be known, your life will definitely suck while you grind away in misery.The questing is pretty standard in this game. Collect X of these, Kill Y of those, etc etc. While this is a tried and true method, it is dull BUT it works! Each individual also has 'FEATS' which are a set of instance quests you don't have to pick up, they are already in journal, you just have to complete them in a single run of each particular instance. They reward you with items, gold, and XP. Overall, questing/FEATs are simple and effective and lend to leveling quite well.I won't comment on the classes because they lend to your particular playstyle. Warcaster has more summons of ""creatures"". Eidolon has a mix of spells and summons. And the Elementalist, lots of spells and some pretty awesome creatures. To each his own in this aspect, you decide, I am not biased in the least.The gameplay is smooth with nifty animations and has been completely lag-free for me. The game isn't graphically intensive so those of your running your mother's old toaster, you should be just fine! +1 in my book.There is an in-game auction (Broker). Works as intended, helps to get whatever you may need. +1No bank/storage as of yet, however you can buy 5 bag upgrades. Each bag holds 20 items I believe? So yeah, 100 damn things, that's plenty. Push comes to shove, make a mule. So this is one of those in the middle things. I don't feel strongly for or against.The biggest issues this game is suffering from right now though, is a lack of players. If this game was vitalized by a healthy surge of players, I can easily seeing it being a niche title with a fair playerbase if people would just give it a shot. I said what the hell for $3.50 and you know what? It was well worth it. (Cough it up, cheapskates! You don't need to go buy another pack of smokes, buy this instead.)Overall, this game is a decent instance dungeon-crawler, hack/slash (per say) with definite needs for strategy. I would definitely recommend the Steam community give this a whirl, as it isn't as bad as one might think.TL;DR - Instance-based dungeon crawler with random ""deck"" of spells/summons, need for strategy, and a fun game. Polish is definitely here, needs a little more (but what doesn't?) and a great MMO in the vein of Path of Exile/Diablo.Thanks for reading!"
